defs.docs: This crate contains a JPEG decoder.

defs.name: L8
defs.docs: Luminance (grayscale), 8 bits

defs.name: RGB24
defs.docs: RGB, 8 bits per channel

defs.name: CMYK32
defs.docs: CMYK, 8 bits per channel

defs.name: PixelFormat
defs.docs: An enumeration over combinations of color spaces and bit depths a pixel can have.

defs.name: ImageInfo
defs.docs: Represents metadata of an image.

defs.name: width
defs.docs: The width of the image, in pixels.

defs.name: height
defs.docs: The height of the image, in pixels.

defs.name: pixel_format
defs.docs: The pixel format of the image.

defs.name: Decoder
defs.docs: JPEG decoder

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `Decoder` using the reader `reader`.

defs.name: info
defs.docs: Returns metadata about the image.

defs.name: read_info
defs.docs: Tries to read metadata from the image without decoding it.

defs.name: decode
defs.docs: Decodes the image and returns the decoded pixels if successful.

defs.name: Hierarchical
defs.docs: Hierarchical JPEG.

defs.name: Lossless
defs.docs: Lossless JPEG.

defs.name: ArithmeticEntropyCoding
defs.docs: JPEG using arithmetic entropy coding instead of Huffman coding.

defs.name: SamplePrecision
defs.docs: Sample precision in bits. 8 bit sample precision is what is currently supported.

defs.name: ComponentCount
defs.docs: Number of components in an image. 1, 3 and 4 components are currently supported.

defs.name: DNL
defs.docs:
An image can specify a zero height in the frame header and use the DNL (Define Number of
 Lines) marker at the end of the first scan to define the number of lines in the frame.

defs.name: SubsamplingRatio
defs.docs: Subsampling ratio.

defs.name: NonIntegerSubsamplingRatio
defs.docs: A subsampling ratio not representable as an integer.

defs.name: UnsupportedFeature
defs.value: UnsupportedFeature::{Hierarchical, Lossless, ArithmeticEntropyCoding, SamplePrecision, ComponentCount, DNL, SubsamplingRatio, NonIntegerSubsamplingRatio}
defs.docs: An enumeration over JPEG features (currently) unsupported by this library.

defs.name: Format
defs.docs:
The image is not formatted properly. The string contains detailed information about the
 error.

defs.name: Unsupported
defs.docs: The image makes use of a JPEG feature not (currently) supported by this library.

defs.name: Io
defs.docs: An I/O error occurred while decoding the image.

defs.name: Internal
defs.docs: An internal error occurred while decoding the image.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs: Errors that can occur while decoding a JPEG image.
